Well... first off I want to say that I really love this company, and I don't want to give it a bad word, so please before you give up on it try the pc version, it is free off bugs and can run smooth and really fast on a hd drive with average computer systems, so take that to mind after I've given this review. Within the app version on phones (not yet tested on tablets but might be the same problems) it is the glitchiest simulator I've ever come across on, and this is using a samsung galaxy s7 on lowest settings possible. I would suggest if you like seeing scenery not bug up and become a massive black hole (about 70% off the scenery you see is) after 5seconds off flight in front off you. This is truly awful and sad part about the android version, but that does not mean the pc version is not, please don't give up hope on this company and if you can, try the flight sim on steam for 1hr and a bit on your pc, I reckon even a i3 could run it with smooth fps at high graphics compared to other simulators. And I'd like to also mention theres no bugs at all on the pc version, do you research on youtube and sim flight reviews before trying it out, you won't be disappointed if you like scenery

I am a private pilot, owned a Cessna 172 and live in the San Francisco Bay Area. I paid the $5 for this sim because I wanted to fly around the San Francisco Bay Area. What I love about it: 1) graphics detail; 2) audio realism (with headphones I felt like I was in the 172); 3) plane handling characteristics (the controls are as close to being in an actual plane as you can get: taxi, take-off, cruise, stalls, landing); and 4) flying in real time around the Bay Area (I flew San Jose to San Francisco. That took me about 30 minutes as I cruised with full flaps, 70% throttle to take in the sights.  I am using a Note 3 which is plenty powerful to run this app at high detail. Flights were smooth and the scenery refreshed quickly.   Others have some complaints, but my comments are based on the fact this is only $5. It is well worth that, especially student pilots who need some 172 time in a simulator. Having owned a 172 I can assure you THIS is as close as you can get to the real deal. And remember, it is only $5 frigging dollars! Fork it over skinflints.

replyContent:
Hello, if you have issues downloading Aerofly 2, please try the following:

1) Goto Settings -> Apps -> Google Play Store
2) Tap on CLEAR DATA and on CLEAR CACHE
3) Tap on FORCE STOP
4) Restart your device and try downloading again
